  "text": "Long-term and heavy consumption of alcohol leads to hepatotoxicity, thus increasing the risk of chronic liver damage [CITATION_1] . The pathogenesis of alcoholic liver disease (ALD) is a result of chronic alcohol usage. In the United States, approximately 44% of the 26,000 reported deaths due to cirrhosis are due to ALD [CITATION_2] . In South Korea, next to Hepatitis B and C, 20% of chronic liver diseases are due to ALD [CITATION_3] . Chronic alcohol consumption is associated with progressive liver disease ranging from ",
